Doctors of South Africa: Although with strong transmission, most of the patients infected by Omicron are mild cases
According to lots of doctors and medical experts in South Africa, most of the patients infected by Omicron are milder cases, although it has faster transmission speed.
According to report from the Associated Press, with the transmission of Omicron in South Africa, as reported by a physician organization composed by more than 5000 doctors in Gauteng, South Africa, most of the current patients of COVID-19 in treatment have mild symptoms, those similar with flu such as body ache and cough.
According to Doctor Unben Pillay, chief inspector of the organizations, he needs to provide medical services to dozens of patients every day, but none of them needs to be hospitalized.
Pillay said: “Their disease can be controlled at home, and most of them can recover after isolation of 10 to 14 days. ”
He said that aged patients or those with health problems were included, who were easier to be caught in severe cases due to infection of the corona virus.
He said, with a comparison, the patients of COVID-19 of the last round of epidemic suffered from “breathing difficulties and low blood oxygen.
Many of them should be hospitalized within only a few days”.
Other doctors shared similar experience within 2 weeks after the first report of the Omicron new variant in South Africa.
Although some more weeks are needed to collect sufficient evidences; observation and early proof of doctors have provided some clues.
According to the summarization made by National Institute of Infectious Diseases of South Africa, among the patients of COVID-19 who were hospitalized within latest weeks, only 30% of them were severe cases, which were a half of the proportion of severe cases of the last round of epidemic; the average stay is reduced from 8 days to 2.8 days; only 3% of the latest patients of COVID-19 died, which was as high as 20% in the cases of early epidemic in South Africa.
By quoting the data from National Institute of Infectious Diseases of South Africa and other reports, Willem Hanekom, director of Africa Institute of Health said: “At present, almost all the traces indicate that this is a relatively mild disease. ”
He also said: “However, it’s the early stage, and we need acquire data of later stage.
In general conditions, hospitalization and death happen later, and it’s just two weeks since we entered into this round of epidemic. ”
At the same time, scientists all over the whole world are observing the number of medical cases and the rate of hospitalization, as well as the effect of the current vaccine and the therapeutic method at present.
Although Delta is still the main COVID-19 viral strain all over the whole world, Omicron cases are emerging in dozens of countries, in which South Africa is the center of the epidemic.
According to introduction from health officials, the new cases detected in Gauteng Province in the first week of December were increased by 400%; according to test results, Omicron variant cases occupied more than 90%.
Review on education: What should we do to rescue abducted children?
As the famous public service advertising says, “there is no killing if there is no buying”; in a good environment with no demand on “abduction”, if people can prevent and fight against abduction, to make it no benefit to acquire, such crime will not happy again.
Recently, the platform for emergency release of missing children information developed by the Crackdown on the Abduction of Criminal Investigation Department of the Ministry of Public Security has been put into operation.
This is an Internet information platform, which is established for releasing information of missing children, so that the abducted children can be found back in time.
With the name of “reunion”, the App is so warm.
With new technological means, the App has not only “artistic” and full of feelings, but also appropriate, practical and effective information means.
In order to fight against abduction, the first objective is to find out the abducted children and ensure their security and freedom.
The judgment and punishment to the criminal suspect is the secondary thing.
With the significance of criminal punishment, there are lots of “major terms” from individual punishment, social prevention to legal education.
However, before solving a case, the most important thing is the safety of the victim.
There are orders of priority; suspend the discussion on topics with large disputes such as “if death penalty shall be sentenced to suspect of abducting children” before “seeking and rescuing” children; rescuing them is the most urgent thing.
According to the experience in solving such cases, traders in human beings usually run away from the crime location as soon as possible.
Therefore, every more minute indicates more difficulty in seeking and rescuing of children and solving of the case.
In this condition, it is a practical action to establish a platform such as “reunion”, so as to provide an effective method to solve the case and find the children.
After all, “crackdown on the abduction” is a big task in need of the operation of the whole legal system.
The care of “protecting children” shall be implemented in improvement on legislation, judicial safeguard and careful enforcement for fighting against crime, protecting rights and benefits of children and parents.
In addition, we can do better to prevent abduction of children from family to the society.
By taking a common case as an example, parents and the child had a rest in the train station, and the parents found their child lost after they woke up.
It is unpractical to expect that a child of 2 years old can protect himself/herself sufficiently; however, as parents of young children, adults shall have at least equivalent protection awareness.
The father and the mother can take turns in sleeping, or they can protect their child in a proper way, which are the elementary approaches for protecting children from being abducted.
Viewing from the other side of crackdown on abduction, the party that purchases the abducted children shall be noticed and punished, too.
Any single illegal behavior is generally one link of a long chain.
According to the Penal Code, in our country, the legal minimum standard for the crime of child abduction is 5 years; suspects with especially serious plots can be sentenced to death penalty, with properties confiscated.
With high minimum standard for the crime and heavy maximum standard, under the trend of the “lightening of punishment”, the crime of child abduction is a crime with relatively heavy sentence.
However, there have been lots of cases of child abduction so far.
It can be seen that some people have outdated ideas and weak legal consciousness in bringing up children.
It is necessary to provide them with legal education.
Strict enforcement of laws is insufficient for effective control of the crime of child abduction.
If the “market” of buying children widely exists, and abductors keep innovating abduction approaches, forming the pattern of “fighting against” law-executors, the crackdown on the abduction will inevitably be of low efficiency.
Therefore, removing outdated ideas and popularizing common legal knowledge contribute to taking a radical cure to child abduction and child buying.
