A girl raised donations for her elder sister by acting a target: "It’s ok since they are flesh wounds" - Xinhuanet
A girl stood in front of a wood board writing “A real person target, 10 yuan for each arrow” in Wulin Square in Hangzhou.
Yesterday morning, a picture of “A girl of Hangzhou raised donations for her elder sister by acting as a target” was spread all over WeChat.
It is shown in the picture that a girl stood in front of a wood board slightly higher than a person writing “A real person target, 10 yuan for each arrow” in Wulin Square in Hangzhou, indicating that people can make the payment and then shoot with a bow and arrows.
The behavior was discussed heatedly by people in the Internet.
Yesterday night, the publicity director of Xiacheng sub-office of Hangzhou Public Security Bureau confirmed to the journalist of the Beijing News that after confirmation by the police, the girl had the behavior in order to raise donations for her elder sister; however, this behavior is not advocated, and the girl left from the local police station yesterday after warning.
The girl who raised donations by acting as a target in the street was warned
In the picture spread in the Internet, a girl with long hair was standing in front of a big wood board writing “A real person target, 10 yuan for each arrow” in black ink in Wulin Square in Hangzhou, and there was another wood board in front of her writing the bank account, WeChat account and Alipay account.
The picture was discussed heatedly after it was spread in the Internet.
According to some people in the Internet, this behavior is “begging behavior grabbing attention”, but some others show sympathy to her.
“We found her at about 10:00 am on the 23rd day of this month when we went on the patrol around the square, and there were lots of onlookers then. ”
According to what the police of the Tianshui Police Station nearby told the local media, there were two young and beautiful girls of their 20s who set up a stall.
In which the girl acting as the “real person target” was keeping crying, and she begged onlookers to pay this game; the other girl was saying that the elder sister of her friend suffered from leucocythemia, in urgent need of operation fee, and she asked onlookers to help her friend.
“We have contacted the police in Guizhou and understand that the girl was raising donations for her elder sister who suffered from leucocythemia. ”
